    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301997">Figure 97</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301997" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301997" filename="../figg13/G1301997.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 97. Synchronizer Assembly Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the larger LO range synchronizer ring on the bench. Cover the assembly with a shop rag
                to prevent losing the three springs released from the high range synchronizer at the pin locations. Pull
                the HI range synchronizer from the blocker pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301998">Figure 98</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301998" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301998" filename="../figg13/G1301998.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 98. Pull HI Range Synchronizer From Blocker Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the sliding clutch from the synchronizer ring LO range pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301999">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301999" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301999" filename="../figg13/G1301999.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 99. Remove Sliding Clutch From Synchronizer Ring LO Range Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
